                'description' => 'Diphtheria is a serious bacterial infection. You can catch it from a person who has the infection and coughs or sneezes. You can also get infected by coming in contact with an object, such as a toy, that has bacteria on it. Diphtheria usually affects the nose and throat. Symptoms include: A thick covering in the back of the throat, A sore throat and hoarseness, Swollen glands (enlarged lymph nodes) in your neck, Difficulty breathing or rapid breathing, Nasal discharge, Fever and chills, Malaise. Diphtheria can lead to breathing problems, paralysis, heart failure, and even death. If your child has this infection, call your doctor. Diphtheria is treated with antibiotics. Vaccines can prevent diphtheria.',
