                'description' => 'Pneumococcal disease is an infection caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae bacteria (“pneumococcus”). These bacteria can cause many types of illnesses, including: Pneumococcal pneumonia, which affects the lungs, Pneumococcal bacteremia, which affects the blood, Pneumococcal meningitis, which affects the coverings of the brain and spinal cord. Pneumococcal disease is common in young children, but older adults are at greatest risk of serious pneumococcal infections and even death. There are two vaccines that help protect against pneumococcal disease: PCV13 and PPSV23. Talk to your or your child’s doctor to find out which pneumococcal vaccines are recommended for you or your child.',
